Flags to add

--no-build       // Spawns the watchdog and automatically uses the vetted / fallback path instead of trying to pull and compile new versions of the app
--insecure       // skips the kernel driver registration and hash integrity checks on startup
--no-kernel      // keeps the hash check but doesn't register with the kernel driver
--no-hash        // keeps the kernel driver in check but doesn't trip it if the hash checks fail
--no-clean       // skips the cargo clean commands once builds are complete (Client apps are exempt, they always need to be clean)
--dummy-ebpf     // forces the application to initialize using the dummy ebpf module even when the platform support the full once
--ledger-awol    // forces the database for the ledger to run with no WAL, it'll be rough on io but good for ledger spot checks
--yap-level X    // a way to set the log mode at calltime using the set_log_level() functions

--client-root    // ignore the forces uid and gid 33 param, and spawn the client applications as the same user we run as
--mock-system    // List system applications that we've validated can be run on this system without building or spawning them, provide some dummy metrics, and keep the status as unknown 
--mock-client    // List client applications that we've validated can be run on this system without building or spawning them, provide some dummy metrics, and keep the status as unknown 
--mock-all       // List All applications that we've validated can be run on this system without building or spawning them, provide some dummy metrics, and keep the status as unknown
--kill-on-drop   // If we fail attempting to re-attach to an orphaned child, run a pkill on the tracked pid then drop it from all stores.

Implemtation notes, This is only meant to be present in debug builds of the application, when any of these flags are passed,
the application should always report its status as tripped and a note like 'DEV arguments passed'. With no arguments passed
a debug build should still show the security as tripped aswell